job.title: ESIC UDC Recruitment 2021 (6552 Vacancies) Steno Notification Apply Online
job.body:
Total Vacancies:6652

Name of the posts:

  • Upper Division Clerk (UDC)/ Stenographer

Description:

The Employees State Insurance Corporation issued a total of 6652 vacancies for the posts of Upper Division Clerk (UDC)/ Stenographer. The online application for the posts of Upper Division Clerk (UDC)/ Stenographer under ESIC shall start soon. The eligible candidates must submit the online application before 31-05-2021. Check the complete details below so that all the doubts about the filling of the online application get cleared. For more such updates do visit theprograd.com.The ProGrad jobs.

 

Mode of application & application fee:

The mode of application is online and after filling in the required details you have to provide the billing details for the application fee.

  • Shall be available soon
  • For more details, you can refer to the notification. The link is given at the bottom.

Important dates:

  • The Last date to apply for this online application form is 31-05-2021

Educational qualification:

To apply for the posts issued by the ESIC you must have fallen in the educational criteria given below:

  • You must have complete your Graduation to apply for the post of Upper Division Clerk (UDC)/ Stenographer  

Age limit criteria:

To apply for this job you must have fallen in the age limit criteria provided by the ESIC :

  • The minimum age limit to apply is: 18years
  • The maximum age limit to apply is: 27years
  • For age relaxation criteria you can refer to the notification given below in The ProGrad jobs.

Pay Scale:

  • The pay scale as per 7th pay commission for the post of Upper Division Clerk (UDC)/ Stenographer is: As per norms

Check the detailed notification also if we missed something

Detailed vacancies:

The vacancies in detail are given below. Check below that Employees State Insurance Corporation issued this notification for which posts.

How to apply for ESIC Recruitment 2021?

  • First, visit the official website.
  • Register yourself on the portal of ESIC.
  • Login yourself on the portal.
  • Find the notification of the Upper Division Clerk (UDC)/ Stenographer.
  • Fill up the complete details that are asked in the application form.
  • Upload your photo and signature with the dimensions asked in the instructions.
  • Submit the application fee
  • Finally, download the application form for future needs.

How to prepare for ESIC UDC?

Try this strategy to crack any exam:

  • You must have the syllabus.
  • Give a brief reading of the syllabus.
  • Buy a previous year's papers book.
  • See the most frequent topics that came in previous papers.
  • First, finish them and revise them on daily basis.
  • The final and most important steps are to revise, revise and revise.
